### Premium flow manual test
### Purpose:
### 1) create free session/report token
### 2) create PENDING order without PG approval
### 3) force the order to PAID in DB
### 4) save paid survey
### 5) run generate -> finalize -> status
### 6) open /r/{token}
###
### Important:
### - This file follows the current project routes and models exactly.
### - Real premium access checks still run. You must manually flip orders.status to PAID in DB after the prepare step.
### - sid comes from /api/survey/free
### - report_token is the same as free_token from /api/survey/free
### - order_id comes from /api/payments/inicis/prepare response.form.oid

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@buyerName = Premium Flow Test
@buyerEmail = premium-flow-test@example.com
@buyerTel = 010-1234-5678

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) Free survey
### Expected:
### - 200 OK
### - body.sid is created
### - body.free_token is created
### - body.next should be PAY for this payload
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/survey/free
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schema_version": "survey_v1",
  "stage": "free",
  "answers": {
    "FREE_Q1_stop_work_7d": 1,
    "FREE_Q2_sns_check_yesterday": 1,
    "FREE_Q3_impulse_control_rate": 90,
    "FREE_Q4_main_fear": "fear_abandonment",
    "FREE_Q5_red_flags": ["rf_none"]
  },
  "contact": {
    "phone": "01012345678",
    "email": "premium-flow-test@example.com"
  },
  "consent": {
    "privacy_consent": true
  }
}

> {% 
client.global.set("sid", response.body.sid);
client.global.set("report_token", response.body.free_token);
%}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) Create order in PENDING state
### Expected:
### - 200 OK
### - body.ok = true
### - body.form.oid is the new order_id
### - DB orders.status should be PENDING
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/inicis/prepare
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reportToken": "{{report_token}}",
  "buyerName": "{{buyerName}}",
  "buyerEmail": "{{buyerEmail}}",
  "buyerTel": "{{buyerTel}}"
}

> {% 
client.global.set("order_id", response.body.form.oid);
%}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) Stop here and run SQL manually
### Use one of these files:
### - sql/test_premium_flow_postgres.sql
### - sql/test_premium_flow_sqlite.sql
###
### Required manual DB update:
### - orders.status -> PAID
### - orders.paid_at -> current time
### - keep orders.sid and reports.sid matched
###
### After the SQL update, continue below.
### ------------------------------------------------------------

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) Access check after manual PAID update
### Expected:
### - 200 OK
### - body.ok = true
### - If false/NOT_PAID, the DB update was not applied correctly
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/access-check?token={{report_token}}&orderId={{order_id}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) Save paid survey
### Expected:
### - 200 OK
### - body.ok = true
### - body.sid should match the sid captured from step 1
### - body.next = GENERATE_REPORT
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/survey/paid
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schema_version": "paid_survey_v1",
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}",
  "answers": {
    "q1": "stable",
    "q2": "dating_clear",
    "q3": "once",
    "q4": "w2_4",
    "q5": "w1",
    "q6": "other",
    "q7": "fight",
    "q8": "mid",
    "q9": "mixed",
    "q10": "pursue_avoid",
    "q11": "need_time",
    "q12": "press",
    "q13": "partial_open",
    "q14": "small_response",
    "q15": "once_twice",
    "q16": "mixed",
    "q17": "m50_70",
    "q18": ["sns_stalk", "write_delete"],
    "q19": ["sleep_appetite", "focus_down"],
    "q20": "reconcile",
    "notes": "manual premium flow test"
  }
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) Generate preview payload
### Expected:
### - 200 OK
### - body.ok = true
### - body.prompt exists
### - body.metrics exists
### - DB report is not finalized yet in this step
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 7) Finalize premium report
### Expected:
### - 200 OK when OPENAI_API_KEY is configured and the LLM call succeeds
### - body.status = READY
### - body.saved = true
### - body.markdown and body.html are not empty
### - DB reports.status should become READY
###
### Failure expectation:
### - 502 LLM_CALL_FAILED if OPENAI_API_KEY is missing/invalid or network call fails
### - DB reports.status should become FAILED in that case
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}",
  "overwrite": true
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 8) Check report status
### Expected after successful finalize:
### - 200 OK
### - body.status = READY
### - body.has_html = true
### - body.has_markdown = true
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/status?sid={{sid}}&order_id={{order_id}}&report_token={{report_token}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### 9) Rendered report page
### Expected after successful finalize:
### - 200 OK
### - HTML page rendered from reports.html
###
### Note:
### - Current route is /r/{token}
### - /report?token=... also exists, but /r/{token} is the public short path returned by the premium status meta/report URL pattern
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/r/{{report_token}}

### ============================================================
### Failure cases
### ============================================================

@missing_report_token = t_free_missing_token_for_manual_test
@missing_order_id = RCL_missing_order_for_manual_test
@unpaid_order_id = RCL_unpaid_manual_test
@mismatch_order_id = RCL_mismatch_manual_test
@ready_reuse_order_id = {{order_id}}
@ready_reuse_report_token = {{report_token}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F1) order_id / report_token mismatch
### Purpose:
### - verify that premium endpoints reject an order that belongs to a different sid
### Execution condition:
### - create another paid order/report pair in DB and set @mismatch_order_id to an order_id that belongs to another sid
### - keep @ready_reuse_report_token pointing to the successful token from the normal flow
### Expected status code:
### - 400
### Expected response:
### - detail = REPORT_ORDER_MISMATCH
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{mismatch_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{ready_reuse_report_token}}"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F2) NOT_PAID on generate
### Purpose:
### - verify payment gate before report generation
### Execution condition:
### - create a new order with /api/payments/inicis/prepare and do not run the FORCE PAID SQL
### - set @unpaid_order_id to that order_id
### - use a real report_token that matches the same sid as the unpaid order
### Expected status code:
### - 403
### Expected response:
### - detail = NOT_PAID
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{unpaid_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F3) NOT_PAID on finalize
### Purpose:
### - verify payment gate before final report generation
### Execution condition:
### - same as F2
### Expected status code:
### - 403
### Expected response:
### - detail = NOT_PAID
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{unpaid_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}",
  "overwrite": true
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F4) non-existent report_token on generate
### Purpose:
### - verify invalid token handling
### Execution condition:
### - none
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = INVALID_REPORT_TOKEN
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{missing_report_token}}"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F5) non-existent report_token on finalize
### Purpose:
### - verify invalid token handling on finalize
### Execution condition:
### - none
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = INVALID_REPORT_TOKEN
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{missing_report_token}}",
  "overwrite": true
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F6) overwrite=false should reuse existing READY report
### Purpose:
### - verify reuse path in finalize when html/markdown already exist
### Execution condition:
### - normal flow must already have completed successfully
### - reports.status must already be READY and html/markdown must be non-empty
### Expected status code:
### - 200
### Expected response:
### - ok = true
### - saved = false
### - status = READY
### - meta.reused_existing = true
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{ready_reuse_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{ready_reuse_report_token}}",
  "overwrite": false
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F7) paid survey missing on generate
### Purpose:
### - verify paid survey requirement before preview generation
### Execution condition:
### - create a new free survey -> prepare -> FORCE PAID
### - do not call /api/premium/survey/paid for that sid
### - set @ready_reuse_report_token and @ready_reuse_order_id to that new pair only for this test, or create separate variables manually
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = PAID_SURVEY_NOT_FOUND
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{ready_reuse_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{ready_reuse_report_token}}"
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F8) paid survey missing on finalize
### Purpose:
### - verify paid survey requirement before final generation
### Execution condition:
### - same as F7
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = PAID_SURVEY_NOT_FOUND
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{ready_reuse_order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{ready_reuse_report_token}}",
  "overwrite": true
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F9) overwrite=true on an already READY report
### Purpose:
### - verify explicit regeneration path on existing READY report
### Execution condition:
### - normal flow must already have completed successfully
### - report must already be READY
### Expected status code:
### - 200 on successful LLM call
### Expected response:
### - ok = true
### - saved = true
### - status = READY
### - meta.reused_existing should not be present on this path
### ------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_id": "{{order_id}}",
  "report_token": "{{report_token}}",
  "overwrite": true
}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F10) status query when report does not exist
### Purpose:
### - verify invalid token handling on status endpoint
### Execution condition:
### - none
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = INVALID_REPORT_TOKEN
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/status?sid={{sid}}&order_id={{order_id}}&report_token={{missing_report_token}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### F11) status query when order does not exist
### Purpose:
### - verify missing order handling on status endpoint
### Execution condition:
### - none
### Expected status code:
### - 404
### Expected response:
### - detail = ORDER_NOT_FOUND
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/premium/report/status?sid={{sid}}&order_id={{missing_order_id}}&report_token={{report_token}}


